<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-10-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-10-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="1825" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1825">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 319.1123L25/22.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Minister <persName type="to">Price</persName>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 197.]</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-10-28">
                                        <hi rend="italic">October 28, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your No.
                                637, of the 7th instant, enclosing a copy of a note addressed by you
                                to the Panaman Foreign Office requesting further information
                                relative to the prosecutions by the Government of Panama against the
                                policeman and others on account of the Colon riot of April 2
                                last.</p>
                            <p>Your action is approved.</p>
                            <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Frank L. Polk.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>